      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">The Origin</h2>
      <p>OTP started with a question: if everything about how your AI team operates were lost, what single artifact would contain enough intelligence to rebuild it?</p>
      <p>That question came from running 14 AI agents in production at <strong>Sneeze It</strong>, a digital agency. Agents named Radar (Chief of Staff), Dan (Strategic Co-Founder), Dash (Performance Analyst), Pepper (Executive Assistant), Crystal (Project Manager), Dirk (Revenue Operator), Jeff (Chief Information Officer), Neil (Chief Learning Officer), and more. Each with a clear seat, clear tools, and clear accountability.</p>
      <p>The coordination rules that kept them from colliding lived in a single document. We called it the Organizational Operating System. When we started sharing it, other organizations wanted to compare theirs. OTP was born.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">The Mission</h2>
      <p>Every organization running AI agents is solving the same coordination problems from scratch. Which agent owns what? How do they share data without conflicts? Where does human oversight begin and end? What happens when rules are violated?</p>
      <p>These answers exist, scattered across thousands of organizations. OTP makes them visible, comparable, and learnable. We call this <a href="/glossary#coordination-intelligence" class="text-otp-500 hover:text-otp-600">coordination intelligence</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">The Stack</h2>
      <p>AI coordination happens at three layers:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>MCP</strong> (Model Context Protocol): Agent-to-Tool. How agents access external capabilities.</li>
        <li><strong>A2A</strong> (Agent-to-Agent): Agent-to-Agent. How agents negotiate and hand off work.</li>
        <li><strong>OTP</strong> (Organization Transport Protocol): Org-to-Intelligence. How organizations encode and share coordination patterns.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>MCP and A2A are infrastructure. OTP is intelligence. The three layers are complementary. <a href="/glossary#three-layer-stack" class="text-otp-500 hover:text-otp-600">Learn more about the stack</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">Built by the System It Measures</h2>
      <p>OTP was built using the same AI agent coordination system it is designed to measure. The platform was constructed in 48 hours by a team of AI agents following the rules documented in their own OOS. This is recursive credibility: the system works because it was built by the system. <a href="/blog/built-in-48-hours" class="text-otp-500 hover:text-otp-600">Read the build story</a>.</p>

